title: Optimized polarimetry for polarization-transfer experiments with protons and deuterons

experiments with protons and deuterons

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.A, Vol.327, p.441 (1993)

x4freetext: Four pairs of silicon surface barrier detectors
mounted symmetrically to the beam axis.
An additional detector mounted at 20.degr.(lab) was
used as a target thickness monitor.
The reactions He-4(p,p)He-4, C-12(p,p)C-12 and
3He(d,p)4He are used as analyzers. The new polarimeter
was used for a measurement of the polarization-transfer
coefficients K(Y) and K(z) of the reaction D(p,p)D at
E(p)=19 MeV.
The number of counts in the elastic peak was corrected
for background and dead time.
Uncertainty in carbon peak separation
from oxygen peak.
The errors due to geometrical
uncertainties of the polarimeter and detector setup
and of the beam position
Tabulated data were obtained from NNDC

x4freetext: A self-supporting C-12 foil with a thickness of
approximately 100 mug/cm**2 was used.
the errors of the relative cross sections
consisted of statistical and geometrical errors (0.003
mm for aperture uncertainty and 0.5 mm for aperture
position) and errors from variations of target and beam
position (2mm beam shift with spot diameter of 2 mm and
1 mm target position variation). They reach their
maximum value of 0.6% at the extreme scattering angles
30. and 145. degr.
Total errors between 4% and 6% in cross section
The cross sections were normalized to
absolute measurements
